  "prompt": "Is the correct term, \"I used to be\" or \"I use to be\"?",
  "response": "The correct term is \"I used to be.\"\n\n\"Used to\" is the standard way to describe a past habit or state that no longer continues. For example:\n- \"I used to live in New York.\"\n- \"She used to play tennis every weekend.\"\n\n\"Use to\" (without the -d) is incorrect in standard English. The only time \"use to\" might appear is in questions or negative statements with \"did\":\n- \"Did you use to play soccer?\"\n- \"I didn't use to like vegetables.\"\n\nBut in standard statements, always use \"used to.\"",
